DESCRIPTION:Neighborhoods: Capitol Hill\,Central Area/Squire Park\,First Hi
	ll\,Judkins Park\,Madison Park\,Madrona/Leschi\,Montlake/Portage BayEvent 
	Types: Community\,Education\,Hobbies\,Holiday/Seasonal Events\, Sports/Rec
	reation\,Youth\n\nAudience: Children\,Special Needs\,Teen\n\nS ponsoring O
	rganization: 3x3 Basketball Association \\(3XBA\\)\n\nContact: Lakin Rolan
	d\n\nContact Email: info@3xba.com\n\nPre-Register: Yes\n\nCost: $250 \\+ f
	ees\n\nRegistration Details: Two sessions offered each Sunday: Grades 2-5 
	from 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM\, Grades 6-8 from 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM. The clinic
	 runs for five Sundays: March 22\, March 29\, April 5\, Apr il 26\, and Ma
	y 3\, 2026 at The Bush School\, Seattle. Early bird pricin g ends on March
	 1. Learn more about 3xBA and register at: https://www.3xba.com/register\n
	\nLink: https://3xba.ludus.com/index.php?show\\_id=200517791\n\nHelp your 
	athlete grow their game this spring with the 3xBA Spring 3x3 Clinic Series
	-a 5-week program combining fun\, competit ive 3x3 basketball with small-g
	roup instruction led by 3xBA coaches. Players develop skills\, confidence\
	, and basketball IQ through structured play and hands-on coaching. Open to
	 all experience levels for 2nd-8th graders. Athletes should bring a basket
	ball and water bottle. Perfe ct for off-season development and team-style 
	competition.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/3xba-spring-
	3x3-clinic-series/18374377/2026-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdo
	ors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/3xba-spring-3x3-clinic-se
	ries/18374377/2026-03-29T00
